365.2564 days is the [sidereal](sidereal time) orbit. Tropical orbit is 365.2422 days.

## Julian

Julius Caesar assumed the year to take 365.25 days. That's when leap years every four years were added.

## Gregorian

Pope Gregory XIII (1582) Made the correction for 0.0078 day. That's when lack of leaps was established on every century, except ones that also divide by 400.

